helpsearch.question: I have purchased the Ola scooter in EV Mart but need to make changes in my booking, how should I do that?
helpsearch.answer: You may change your registration details (name and address) and vehicle preference details (variant and colour) for each of your reservations via the EV Mart. You cannot however, transfer a reservation from one phone number to another. Registration details and the vehicle colour can be modified till the time of balance payment. The vehicle variant can only be changed before making the full payment.

helpsearch.question: Where can I get this upgrade done?
helpsearch.answer: The front fork arm can be upgraded at specific Ola Experience Centres. You need to book an appointment through the Ola Electric App and provide your location. The nearby centres which are conducting the activity will be visible to you. You can select your preferred centre and book an available date. If there are no centres in your city, you can schedule a time for the Ola team to upgrade the front fork arm of your Ola Scooter at your home. Home service option is also available to those who have purchased the Ola Care+ subscription.

helpsearch.question: What is State subsidy? Is the price included in the invoice?
helpsearch.answer: Similar to the FAME II subsidy provided by the Central Govt., the State subsidy is provided by the respective State Govt. to promote the purchase of electric vehicles. Each state has their own EV policies, which may or may not include a subsidy. The State subsidy amount needs to be claimed separately, post the delivery of the Ola scooter. However for Meghalaya, your final payment amount would include the subsidy benefit.

helpsearch.question: Do I need to replace the front fork arm of my scooter?
helpsearch.answer: Hi, This is a voluntary upgrade being provided to our customers as part of our continuous engineering and design improvement process, we have upgraded the front fork design to enhance the durability and strength even further. Please be assured that this upgrade does not imply that your Ola Scooter is defective, rather, this is a proactive step taken by us to ensure that our customers continue to ride worry free.
